.SH "NAME"
BSON::Timestamp \- BSON type wrapper for timestamps
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version v1.12.2
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use BSON::Types \*(Aq:all\*(Aq;
\&
\&    bson_timestamp( $seconds );
\&    bson_timestamp( $seconds, $increment );
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module provides a \s-1BSON\s0 type wrapper for a \s-1BSON\s0 timestamp value.
.PP
Generally, it should not be used by end-users, but is provided for
backwards compatibility.
.SH "ATTRIBUTES"
.IX Header "ATTRIBUTES"
.SS "seconds"
.IX Subsection "seconds"
A value representing seconds since the Unix epoch.  The default is
current value of \f(CW\*(C`time()\*(C'\fR.
.SS "increment"
.IX Subsection "increment"
A numeric value to disambiguate timestamps in the same second.  The
default is 0.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS "\s-1TO_JSON\s0"
.IX Subsection "TO_JSON"
If the \f(CW\*(C`BSON_EXTJSON\*(C'\fR option is true, returns a hashref compatible with
MongoDB's extended \s-1JSON\s0 <https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/master/source/extended-json.rst>
format, which represents it as a document as follows:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    {"$timestamp" : { "t":<seconds>, "i":<increment> }}
.Ve
.PP
If the \f(CW\*(C`BSON_EXTJSON\*(C'\fR option is false, an error is thrown, as this value
can't otherwise be represented in \s-1JSON.\s0
